node.text: Climbing legends @alexhonnold and @tommycaldwell join us to discuss #sportclimbing’s Olympic debut at #Tokyo2020, what makes climbing so special and who to watch for at the #Olympics #StrongerTogether @ifsclimbing

node.text:
On Day 11, records were smashed in the 400m hurdles, tears were shed in the boxing and Swedish dreams were fulfilled in the pole vault. If you didn’t catch today’s action, where were you?!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
You won't want to miss tomorrow's drama, so check out the full schedule by clicking the link in our bio. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#Tokyo2020

node.text:

#StrongerTogether

node.text:
Elaine Thompson-Herah does it again! It is the double-double for the Jamaican sprint queen in 21.53s! 🇯🇲 

🥇Women’s 200m Tokyo 2020
🥇 Women’s 100m Tokyo 2020
🥇 Women’s 200m Rio 2016
🥇 Women’s 100m Rio 2016

A M A Z I N G.

@WorldAthletics | #StrongerTogether | #Tokyo2020

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Olympic Games on August 03, 2021 tagging @usagym, @teamusa, @simonebiles, and @figymnastics. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text:
We are so much stronger together. ⁠⁠
The women's balance beam final at #Tokyo2020 showed us the strength that can be forged when we support each other, the power of speaking up when you're not okay, and that at the end of the day, gymnastics is a total VIBE! @simonebiles got to see her dogs (in placards of course), IOC President Thomas Bach appeared to give the Olympic Champion a gift for her courage and it was total domination for the People's Republic of China as Guan Chenchen and Tang Xijing embrace over almost flawless routines. Link in bio for the roundup of this heartwarming final. ⁠⁠😍🤍
⁠⁠
#Olympics #gymnastics

node.text:
What a final! Guan Chenchen 🇨🇳 and Tang Xijing 🇨🇳 clinch gold and silver, and Simone Biles 🇺🇸 secures the bronze medal upon her return to the gym at #Tokyo2020 for the women's balance beam final!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Congratulations!⁠⁠
#StrongerTogether #gymnastics #Olympics

node.text:
Smiles, style, swagger. She’s back! @simonebiles is at the Ariake Gymnastics Centre and ready to compete for @usagym in the women’s balance beam event in artistic gymnastics. 
The American is looking for what would be a seventh Olympic medal.

@Figymnastics⁠⁠
#StrongerTogether⁠⁠
#Tokyo2020 #gymnastics
